SYMPTOM_TEXT: As soon as I took the vaccine shot I had an immediate headache, after taking the vaccine I took Tylenol and slept in the rest of the day. The next day I woke up and my arm was red and swollen. I was running fever, still had the headache and now blurry vision. My entire body was hurting. My left side of my body felt numb and tingling. The next two days the pain became worse. I did not really have an appetite. When I did eat I could barely hold my food down. On Wednesday morning I could barely get out of bed, I also felt extreme pain in my lower legs, stabbing pain in stomach and right lower side. I also had ringing in my ears, more in the right ear. I then notice a bruise on my left leg, that it was not originally there, and was also tender to touch. I went to the emergency room on the same day and I was admitted. I was in there for 4 days, they tested my leg and stated it was not a blood clot, although it look and felt like one. They discharge me and advise me that it was a migraine that was causing all my pain.  This was on Sunday, I had a follow up with my PCP on the Friday, however to being in so much pain and shortness of breath, and arm pain I was advise to go to the ER on the Thursday and was admitted again. I was told in the ER I had a blood clot in my right arm and it was most likely from the IV from the previous visit. My blood pressure and heart rate was so high that they put me on medication. No matter the pain medication they gave me, it would not completely take the pain away. They discharge me again on Monday and after me begging them to get run any and all test, they said they found nothing. I'm still in the same amount of pain and same symptoms, still having trouble keeping my food down. The only thing that changed is my left arm is not as sore, however I still have a huge knot and its still warm to touch. I don't know what else to do that is why im contacting the CDC for help. I'm in a extreme amount of pain and pounding headaches.  Please help
OTHER_MEDS: Whelchol, Symbicort, Vitamin C, blackseed Oil

SYMPTOM_TEXT: EXTREME chills and fever.  Alternated 4 or 5 cycles. I thought I was convulsing until I realized I could control it with my breathing. I was shivering so hard that I bit my tongue several times.  I didn't have much energy so it took several minutes before I could grab blankets and even longer before I could close the window.  I was wrapped in several layers of blankets and was still shivering until I fell asleep.  I woke up again and my blankets were soaked in my sweat.  This cycle got more and more intense until the next day.  *I've been hospitalized with pneumonia and this felt 100 times worse. The next day, I had the worst diarrheic that I've ever had, sudden urge.. barely made it to toilet and INSTANTLY discharged what felt like a gallon of brown liquid (it was probably less but felt pretty nasty).

As a result of the manufacture, marketing, advertising, promotion, distribution and/or sale of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine, the patient sustained severe and permanent personal injuries. Further, as a tragic consequence of zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX) vaccine, the patient suffered serious, progressive, permanent, and incurable injuries. The outcome of the event of shingles was considered as not recovered. The reporter considered the event to be related to zoster vaccine live (ZOSTAVAX).  Upon internal review, the event of shingles was considered to be disabling event.

HEART STARTED RACING; LIPS FELT NUMB; LIGHT HEADED; LIPS FELT TINGLY; BLOOD PRESSURE INCREASED TO 145-165/120-135; OXYGEN SATURATION DECREASED; This spontaneous report received from a patient concerned a patient of unspecified age and sex. The patient's height, and weight were not reported. The patient's past medical history included appendix surgery, and concurrent conditions included blood pressure fluctuation (on MAR-2021, the patient's blood pressure (BP) was 110-115), and seasonal allergies. 09-APR-2021, patient took an antihistamine (Allegra) for seasonal allergies before vaccine shot. The patient received covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s (suspension for injection, route of admin, and batch number were not reported) dose was not reported, frequency 1 total, administered on 09-APR-2021 at 10:15 for prophylactic vaccination. The batch number was not reported and has been requested. Concomitant medications included fexofenadine hydrochloride for seasonal allergies. On 09-APR-2021, within the first 15 minutes of vaccination, the patient felt numb and tingly lips and was light headed. The patient waited another 30 minutes at the vaccine center just to be sure symptoms should not progress further. The patient was light headed all day. On same day around 21:00, while laying in bed, patients heart started racing. As patient had pulse oximeter at home so used and resting heart rate was 115 and oxygen level 91. It was reported that patients normal heart rate and oxygen usually remains 75-80 and 95-97 respectively. Patients' blood pressure (BP) had been normal to low all of life, so the sudden spike was completely uncharacteristic. Then Patient called an ambulance at that time patients BP was 145-165/120-135. On 10-APR-2021, initially patient declined to go to hospital, but as patients heart rate was so bad then went to emergency room (ER). The patient waited from 12-4 a.m, but hospital was overrun so not got admitted. So checked BP every hour and it was consistently not drop below 145 systolic and heart rate was over 115. Then patient went to home. On 10-APR-2021, all day, patients heart rate was high, so patient bought a BP cuff to test BP, and it was still 145 systolic range. On 10-APR-2021 at night the patients BP and heart rate started to come down to 135/95.  The action taken with covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s was not applicable. The patient was recovering from heart started racing, and blood pressure increased to 145-165/120-135, and the outcome of lips felt numb, light headed, lips felt tingly and oxygen saturation decreased was not reported.  This report was serious (Other Medically Important Condition).; Sender's Comments: V0 :-covid-19 vaccine ad26.cov2.s -blood pressure increased to 145 -165/120-135. This event is considered not related. The event has a compatible/suggestive temporal relationship, is unlabeled, and has unknown scientific plausibility. There are other factors more likely to be associated with the event than the drug. Specifically: MEDICAL HISTORY, UNDERLYING DISEASE.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Hello! I had my first dose of the Pfizer shot on Sunday, 4/18/21.  Everything was fine.  Then, this past Saturday, 4/24/21, six days later, I woke up with awful chills and aches.  I went to be tested at the Clinic with the rapid test.  The result was negative, but the NP said to quarantine and to get tested again in three days just to make sure.  Later that day, my fever went up to almost 102.  I had a dry cough throughout the day and some shortness of breath.  I was sick until later that afternoon, when my symptoms dissipated after taking Tylenol.  I was fine from then forward..  I quarantined and did the test yesterday through Medical Center. (They give both the rapid and the regular.)  The rapid test result was "presumptive negative." Today, I got the results of the regular test,,and it was also negative.  I'm very happy about this, but I wanted you to know, because I read that though it's rare, some people can have after effects of the shot almost a week after.   (I had no immediate effects after the shot other than my arm was very sore.) I think this is what happened to me. I had no other symptoms Saturday other that the ones I described above.  I wanted you to know for record-keeping purposes in case in you need the info. for COVID-19 research or other purposes.  I'm fine now.  Thanks!

On Wednesday, April 28, 2021 client received his first dose of Pfizer COVID vaccine (LOT #: EW0179) at approximately 11:00am. While in Observation Area, at approximately 11:10am, client came to EMT and stated he felt a sensation that his "heart rate was elevated" & "feeling dizzy." Client was sat immediately in gravity chair and initial set of vitals taken. At 11:15am vitals: BP 162/92, HR: 86, O2 sat: 98%. Upon assessment by EMT & Lead RN, client's medical history includes high blood pressure and diabetes with no history of allergies. Client takes Metformin 1000mg for high blood sugar and Clonidine for high blood pressure which he took this morning at 10am. Client stated to Lead RN and EMT that his blood pressure normally is elevated and he was "feeling anxious" about getting his first COVID vaccine. At 11:20am: BP: 160/80, HR: 95, O2 sat: 99%. At 11:25am: BP: 177/92, HR 109, O2: 99%. At 11:30am: BP: 177/102, HR: 88, O2 sat: 98%. Client states he is "feeling better" and presenting well. At 11:35am: BP: 177/91, HR: 105, O2 sat: 99%, temp: 97%. After 30 minutes of observation, vitals at 11:43 were as follows: BP: 166/82, HR: 90, O2 sat: 98%. Final set of vitals were taken at 11:46am: BP: 162/89, HR: 100, O2 sat: 99%. Client and client's sister who was also present was educated by EMT and Lead RN on signs and symptoms of when to go to the ED/call MD. Lead RN and EMT recommended to client and client's sister to follow up with his primary doctor. Client was able to ambulate to his car with a steady gait at approximately 11:55am  and was driven home by his sister.
OTHER_MEDS: Metformin 1000mg taken at 1000 Clonidine taken at 1000

Patient received J&J COVID vaccine on 4/10/2021. She underwent elective R total knee arthroplasty on 4/20/2021. On 4/21, patient developed chest pain and was found to have a STEMI (large embolus in the posterolateral branch of the right coronary artery). She underwent thrombectomy and angioplasty on 4/21 with no evidence of CAD elsewhere. She developed hypoxic respiratory failure evening of 4/21 and was found to have bilateral pulmonary embolus with saddle type emboli and distal emboli throughout both lungs. She underwent IR guided thrombectomy on4/22 and had a cardiac arrest intra-operatively. Given timing of onset and recent J&J COVID vaccination, the patient was treated with IVIG, steroids, and placed argatroban. She continued to have multiorgan failure requiring mechanical ventilation and hemodialysis. On 4/26, CT head was positive for small area of subarachnoid hemorrhage. Patient was transitioned to comfort care measures and palliatively extubated on 4/26.

A few hours after receiving the first dose of the Pfizer vaccine, I started getting heart palpitations.  My heart felt like it was beating really hard in my chest, and my pulse rate started fluctuating.  I can feel it in my back when I'm sitting in a chair, I can feel it in my neck, and occasionally in my stomach. My pulse rate would go anywhere from low 90s to over 130. There have been some nights where it was difficult to sleep because it was pounding while lying in bed.  Eating seems to flare it up.  It has been three weeks now since the first dose and I am still experiencing bouts of palpitations.  It has settled some, but still comes and goes.  Pulse rate still fluctuating, but not as high.  I am scared to get the second shot, especially considering people are turning up with heart inflammation now.  I am postponing the second dose.  People keep saying the risk of COVID is worse than potential side effects, but this side effect is quite distressing and is affecting my daily life.  I have found groups online where multiple people complain of the exact same thing after getting the pfizer or moderna vaccine.  The general public needs to be made aware there are other potential side effects rather than "flu-like" symptoms.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: No side effects with first shot except arm soreness.  2nd shot was brutal but I think I know why.  I had severe severe muscle ache that Advil could not touch and I could not sleep. The next day I had the flu symptons (feverish, achy (not painful) muscles.  I hate water.  I truly believe the shot dehydrated me and caused the severe muscle pain.  Now that I look back that had to be the problem.  No one has ever described severe muscle pain as a side effect.  Tell people to drink lots of water or gaterade and take two tylenol or ibuprophen.  My husband did both and had not side effects other than a sore arm.  The shots or at least the 2nd shots dehydrate some people.   The next day around 6:30 pm all of my side effects disappeared and I felt great.

I had one large cup of coffee with cream and 3 doughnuts for breakfast approximately 3 hours before the vaccine. I took one Claritin Readitab approximately 2 hours before my vaccine injection to help with pollen allergies.   I was seated during the vaccine injection.  The injection was delivered into upper left arm. I felt fine at first. I stood and exited the room and began speaking with the pharmacist that had delivered the invention to receive instructions. Approximately 2-5 minutes after I received the injection I began to feel dizzy. After approximately 1 minute of dizziness I sat down.  I began to get extremely dizzy to the point of faintness. I noticed during this time that I was getting very sweaty. My skin over my whole body seemed to me to be damp from sweat and where I checked I was sweating visibly (no droplets formed? it was just dampness). At the same time I experienced nausea. I believed that I might throw up, so I requested something to throw up into. I never threw up. I continued to get more and more dizzy and I had trouble remaining upright (while seated). A woman observing me stated afterward that my eyes rolled back and that I fainted. I do not believe that I actually fainted because I remember hearing her tell the pharmacist that I had passed out. I had my eyes closed though, so it is possible that I fainted briefly.  The pharmacist called 911. I began to feel better approximately 15 minutes after receiving the vaccine. I stopped sweating, and then the nausea subsided, and then my dizziness cleared up.   The EMTs arrived approximately 20 minutes after I received the vaccine and took my blood pressure. I do not remember the reading, but the EMT stated that it was not elevated. My blood oxygen was 99%. The EMT waited about 10 minutes and took my blood pressure again. He stated that it was higher, but not concerning. The EMT waited another 10-15 minutes and then left. Before he left, the EMT stated to me that I was one of 2 concurrent calls regarding adverse vaccine responses.   After this event I drank a bottle of  water. It did not seem to have an impact.   I have not received vaccinations since I was a child. I do not remember adverse reactions to injections when I was a child. I did pass out when giving blood approximately 12 years ago. I have always attributed this to the fact that I did not eat or drink for 20 hours prior to donating blood.
ALLERGIES: Aspirin, Penicillin, oil in mango skin

I also contacted my primary care physician, who instructed me the next morning to continue taking one tablet of Benadryl every 6 hours.  The redness around my neck and ears was gone the next morning and the rash on my inner thighs started to disappear.  However, when I let more than 6-8 hours laps between doses of Benadryl, I would feel the itch start to return throughout my body.  This continued for roughly one week. The patient came into the clinic today requesting a COVID vaccine.  He completed an up to date Provider COVID-19 Immunization Consent Form that had been emailed to us from Health Department just this week.  He answered no to all the questions on the form so he was cleared to receive the vaccine.  We currently have Janssen.  The patient received his vaccination via proper procedures and left the clinic.  Upon entering his immunization into AR Web IZ it was noted that he had documentation of having the Moderna series.  The documenation showed one Moderna vaccine on 2-1-21 and the 2nd dose on 3-1-21.  The patient was contacted to verify that the WEB IZ account was his and to see if there had been a clerical error.  The patient confirmed that he had received the Moderna series and he confirmed that the dates sounded right.  The patient stated that he had lost his immunization card with proof of his Moderna vaccines and that he "thought it would be a good idea to just get vaccinated again so he would have proof."  Patient was made aware that he was already considered fully vaccinated before today's dose and that further vaccinations were not recommended.  Patient was made aware that due to the nature of the error and the vaccines being new that our clinic would have to reach out to other sources for guidance in this matter.  Spoke to patient about one hour after his vaccination and at that time he denied any side effects or issues.  Our state immunization department was made aware of the situation.

I wasn't sure if I should report this or not. I mentioned I get intermittent muscle spasms in my leg that aren't even bad enough to complain to my doctor or anything. The night of the first injection I was in bed and a spasm started. I started to get up and it was horrible- it went thru my ***entire*** left leg  - the front and the back and the top and the bottom - the entire leg. I never had anything like that before and since. And it hurt badly. I considered asking my husband to call someone but I went into the bathroom - actually dragging that leg for the most part - and tried putting heat on via my hairdryer. It actually made it worse which is the opposite of what should happen when I usually get anything like that. Then I tried putting on this salve we use for such things made from Arnica called ArnicareCream. It actually helped the spasms completely and I had to keep it bent while the salve worked itself in  - then I could at least walk it off the rest of the way and went back to bed with no issues. I didn't report it to my doctor or anything because I thought maybe it had nothing to do with the shot.  Plus no one else was reporting anything like that - it wasn't in the list of possible side effects.  But it scared me a lot.  I'm only reporting it now because a woman not all that far from us was paralyzed by the shot about 10 hrs later  I think (not the same day and date)  and it sounded somewhat similar in a weird way. It's like the shot "knows" what the bad parts of your body are and hones right in on it. I did not expect to have any issues either. But it seemed much to coincidental that this happened so far only once in my life and on the night of the first shot.  Another minor issue was that my left harm hurt when she jabbed it (second shot did not) and I experienced no pain at all in the arm until a few weeks after the **second** shot which I didn't report. It still intermittently hurts but it feels like it's more related to when I overcarry items, etc.  So again, that might not be anything. Plus I'm at the age where I have rudiments of arthritis most likely.  But the first item was really way out of league with anything I've ever had.
OTHER_MEDS: Lisinopril 12.5MG on pill in the morning
HISTORY: Diagnosed December 2020 with high BP - started Lisinopril immediately then.  Born with some form of torticollis, underwent neck operation in the early 1950's. Appears successful since I walk straight. Have flat feet.  I was hit by a car in the 1980's and it destroyed muscles in my legs and took years for feeling to come back in my calves. I still have some issues with my left leg - particularly my flat feet seem to have never recovered mostly in my left leg. I've been in and out of PT and wearing arch supports.  I get intermittent muscle spasms now in bed if my legs are cold (e.g. the overhead fan is on, etc.) but none that are that bad.. I just get up and try to walk it off.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On the morning of Saturday, March 13th my mother had a CARDIAC ARREST,  luckily i was with her when this happened and called 911 immediately and followed an emergency/cpr protocol.  She had no pulse when the emergency team arrived and they used the defibrillator on her three times in our house before they took her in the ambulance where they used the defibrillator another time.  She was rushed to the Hospital where she was sedated and put on a breathing machine.  It did not seem as if she would survive,  the entire morning was a whirlwind and traumatizing.  In the afternoon they transferred her to the ICU unit.  Luckily after 24 hours they lowered sedation and she had no brain injury etc.,  we were all amazed she was alive. The doctors ran tests etc. to find out what caused this cardiac arrest event,  they found NOTHING - no blood clot, no clogged arteries,  nothing that could have caused this.  My mother also has had not health conditions before this that would have caused this.  She now has a defibrillator implanted and her life will never be the same,  her families either,  we will constantly worry.  I have post traumatic stress from witnessing my mother turn purple and lifeless right in front of my eyes and the emergency team working on her all morning and in the ER. Thank gosh i was with her that morning and that the emergency team arrived within a few minutes or else my mother would not be here today.   The only thing that changed leading up to her Cardiac Arrest was that she got the Pfizer Covid-19 vaccine on February 24th - we need answers,  did the vaccine have anything to do with this?

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received my second shot on April 17th, 2021.  I injured my foot on April 21, 2021.  I went to my General Physician the following day and received a tetanus shot.  Up until that time, my side effects were very light; slight headache, arm muscle pain.  Two days after receiving my tetanus shot I could barely get out of bed.  I woke up feeling as if someone had drugged me; my mind was very fuzzy and it was hard to focus.  Every muscle in my body was in extreme pain and it hurt to breathe.  I had bouts of terrible stomach cramps.  I felt nauseous to the point that I was unable to eat solid food other than chicken soup and crackers for three days.  I do fully believe my side effects happened because of the tetanus shot as I had very little side effects before the shot.  I felt like I was dying.  Luckily I had some medicine at home that helped with the symptoms; gabapentin for my shoulder injury, zofran from a past hospital visit, and I took tylenol.  I am a Medical Assistant and didn't feel the hospital or the Dr. office could have offered me any relief from my symptoms.
OTHER_MEDS: Flonase, Amlopidine, Albuterol inhaler, Symbicort, Singulair, Crestor, Aspirin, Zyrtec, Prilosec
CUR_ILL: Asthma, allergies, Gerd, coronary artery disease

The fever broke around 3:30 or 4 am and I slept through the rest of the night. The next morning 3/09, I felt fatigue, slow, and woozy. I still had chills and muscle aches, although the intensity was less. Halfway through the day the chills intensified, the muscle aches became more severe, and my eyeballs felt like they were burning in the back of my head. By that evening, the fever was back and I couldn?t think straight. My legs ached with a pain that I?ve never felt before. I did not have a severe headache, but I felt that if I exerted myself too much I would get one. My partner said I could barely form coherent sentences, and I was so weak I couldn?t sit up straight. I took 2 more Tylenol that night, went to bed and slept through the whole night. The morning of 3/10 I woke up feeling tired but my skin did not have that feverish feeling. I was no longer sick. On 3/11 I woke up and did my normal morning routine. I ate an egg, some of a Nutella stuffed scone, and drank coffee and water. I took my 3 pills, loratadine, omeprazole, and a probiotic, and I had a severe allergic reaction within 5 minutes of taking the pills. For the next 10 minutes my breathing became labored and wheezy. I experienced severe eosinophilic esophagitis symptoms. For the next week, my EoE symptoms were heightened. I had a reaction after drinking a seltzer water, which does not usually affect me. Within 2 weeks I was back to normal and to my knowledge have not experienced any other related side effects.

Patient had swollen left arm after injection with second vaccine. Patient received first vaccine at mass clinic. She had similar reaction about 24 hours after her first dose on 3/4/2021. She said it went away and about 10 days later came back. She chose to get her second dose at the pharmacy in case it happened again.  The patients arm was swollen and red at injection site and down to above her elbow.  We placed ice on it immediately after patient noticed swelling and redness. After about five minutes it appeared to be getting worse. I moved the patient to a private area and administered diphenydramine 12.5mg/ml at a dose of 50mg. Her husband agreed to drive her home and was present for the entire exchange. She complained she was feeling a bit anxious and I took her blood pressure at 12:11pm it read 194/97 her pulse was 74. Her O2 sat was at 99. I had her stay seated and drink some water.  We went through some breathing exercises and I brought another pharmacist over to talk to her and keep her distracted while I got her a granola bar. I checker her blood pressure again at 12:45pm and it had dropped to 175/93 with a pulse of 72. The swelling and redness in her arm also went down significantly. I told the patient I would check again in 15 minutes if her bp continued to drop and pulse was good I would let them go. She had calmed down a lot at this point and was felling much better. There was only slight redness, which also could have been from the cold ice pack still applied to her arm. At 12:59pm her bp was 164/92 and pulse read 66. The patient agreed to contact me if there were any other issues. They were going to eat at the restaurant next door and check in afterwards if her arm started to swell again. They purchased diphenhydramine and I advised on how to dose. I advised patient to get lots of rest and stay hydrated.
PRIOR_VAX: COVID-19 Moderna, 3/4/21 swollen and red arm

Patient stated she had headache before she came to the pharmacy.  When she contacted us at 1:06pm, she stated her headache was improved, forehead felt numb, upper lips felt numb.  I suggested her to take Benadryl 50 mg and monitored sign/symptoms of allergic reaction, and have someone accompany her and call 911 if needed.  We followed up with patient by phone around 1:32 pm. A few days after receiving the vaccination, I woke up to my face feeling very hot and irritated. I had red, bumpy patches across my cheeks and mostly around the corners of my lips / chin and medial cheeks. For the first few days, the patches were very itchy. I also noticed a few patches pop up along my neck and on my hands, but those disappeared. However, the patches on my face remained.   In the past week (starting around 4/21), the patches lost their bumpiness and became scaly, flaky, and dry, while still being itchy. I started taking Benadryl on 4/26, which has helped with the itchiness, but the patches don't seem to be getting much better despite washing my face twice a day, exfoliating a few times a week, and moisturizing the patches with my normal moisturizer as well as applying Vaseline in the evening hours before bed. Since using Vaseline over the past few nights, the redness has gone down slightly but the flakiness is still prevalent, getting worse throughout the day. The patches look mostly like Seborrheic Dermatitis, a condition I've never had before on any part of my body.   I haven't had an opportunity to see a physician yet, but have ordered some Aveeno eczema creams to try and reduce the flakiness and itchiness. I'm hoping this reaction doesn't occur again with the second shot as it's been very uncomfortable. I also never developed a rash around the injection site.
OTHER_MEDS: I had taken Flucanazole five days prior to having the vaccination and did have an adverse reaction to it (the left side of my lips swelled up) but by the time I received the vaccination, that had subsided.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Patient received first dose of Pfizer around 7:43 AM. Patient observed after vaccine and on her way out felt "her throat feeling thick and itchy". RN brought patient back to med bay. Patient was having difficulty swallowing, and reported throat and tongue itchiness. 50 MG IM Benadryl given at 0813. DOC on call notified at this time. Patient reported symptoms improved after Benadryl, but about 6 minutes later, they came back and felt "worse". Patient was holding her throat, was struggling to swallow, was coughing, and felt SOB. Patient was having difficulty completing a full sentence. Epi pen given at 0823 and 911 called. Patient hospitalized in the past due to anaphylaxis with shellfish. RN monitored patient until EMS arrived at 0837. During that time, patient reported improved symptoms, but still felt it was a little difficult to swallow. Patient awake and alert speaking in full sentences at this time. Denies SOB and VSS. When EMS arrived, patient's symptoms returned and she stated "my throat and muscles in my neck feel swollen and tight. My lips and tongue are itchy and thick". EMS gave another EPI dose at 0847 and transported patient to hospital. Patient was awake and alert prior to transport. EMS arrived on scene at 0837, administered another dose of EPI and transported patient to Hospital.

He was then advised to complete PCR swab and was notified on 12-Apri-21 that his test is positive. As per the protocol, all COVID-19 positive individuals must report to the Health Center within 24 hours of notification and complete 10 days home isolation. During isolation, on 17-Apr-21, patient developed hemoptysis and difficulty breathing a breathing and notified his supervisor who called 112 for an ambulance. He was transferred to  Hospital. His condition started declining on 21-Apr-21 as he became hypoxic and tachypneic and was subsequently sedated and intubated.
